,Recommended,285500,14551334,"Posted: 19 February, 2015",all,Fighter_025,"If you can see past the dated graphics and stilted english then this game is an absolute gem!  I must admit I love cruising around in my modded truck blowing the absolute **** out of bandits.  It takes a little while to get going but once you get to at least your third class of truck, things get really fun.Pros;- Awesome soundtrack- Loads of mods and weapons to chose from- Decent trading system between towns- Large maps to explore- Loads of side quests- Funny dialogueCons;- Funny dialogue and stilted mission/story- Invisible barriers on mountains- No auto-save- Some long back and forth missionsYou can get the general gist of what is going on, but the poor conversion to english (which can be quite funny at times) can detract from the experience.  Otherwise this is a solid game that is fun with an awesome soundtrack.  I would definately buy this game again if they were to ever improve the graphics and perhaps throw in a few more truck classes."
76561198193709158,Recommended,285500,31197230,Posted: 17 April,all,Summerrain,"Sure, this fun little oddity of a game could have used a lot of polish back in the days. But it comes with a truckload of post-apocalyptic charm and has such a stylish dieselpunk vibe to it that you can probably overlook most of its flaws if you have a soft spot for the genre.That said, minor flaws are plenty. Some of them add to the charm, some of them feel like they wasted potential. For a vehicular combat game with plenty of off-road opportunities, the physics are rather simplistic. So are the graphics. The writing feels like they tried to be epic in scope and witty in style, yet it comes across as more of a cheesy translation accident. You get a rather large open world, yet much of the gameplay and storytelling is a lot more linear than you may expect. Towards the middle of the game, all the long-range errand-running starts getting tedious, artificially stretching the game without adding content. They do have a nice choice of vehicles and gear to keep you interested though, even if picking the right truck for the job is usually a no-brainer.Still, Hard Truck Apocalypse basically delivers on its promise. It's fun. It's stylish. It's a very high-concept idea with a very cheesy title, and in many ways, that already tells you a lot about what to expect here."
