,Not Recommended,285500,29263735,Posted: 14 January,all,Krydoza,"I started out recommending this game, then I got to the end and decided to take it away.  The story isn't all that great from the beginning, and the translation is AWFUL, but I was willing to look past that and just enjoy the game for a Car Wars game that it was at heart.  By the time I reached the middle of the story, they toss in a completely disposable story arc into the game to add an additional few hours of gameplay.  Then, when you finally get to the end, instead of tying up loose ends and a decent conclusion, they force you into a one-on-one fight that ends with a scrolling text ending.  WORST ENDING EVER...  OF ALL TIME!= = = = = =Hard Truck/Ex Machina can be described as Mad Max/Car Wars meets Privateer in a devastated Europe.  Hop into a armed and armoured truck and track down the mystery of your past and the world around you.The game starts out where you play merchant and deliver commodities (potatoes, wood, scrap, etc) between towns/villages to earn enough money to repair, fuel, and upgrade your vehicle, while you go from quest point to quest point.  Then things ramp up and you change over to hauling in weapons and commodities salvaged from anyone who attacks you so you can upgrade your weapons and vehicle to survive while moving from quest point to quest point.Play mercenary and destroy outlaws that roam the maps targeting you and other drivers.  Then pick up their loot and sell it to the nearest shop.  Other drivers will help if they stumble onto your fight, and if you are close enough to a fortified town, their turrets will also join in.Play adventurer and take jobs from strangers (mostly found at the bars) to make special deliveries, escort people, etc.What else...  Oh yeah, avenge your adoptive father's death and find out who you really are.You know, when you have the time."
