,Recommended,285500,11873883,"Posted: 26 August, 2014",all,Sperzieb00n,"Horrible title, poor voice acting, and numerous bugs hide a surprisingly underrated game.i have been playing this on windows XP a long time ago but when i switched to windows 7, the game would be missing things ingame, or not work at all.so, what did i do to get it to work on win7?1. unpack the packed gamedatathis appears to fix a lot of loading problems, and made me discover this game actually had weather and a skybox. this process is normally a part of loading but breaks down on many win7 machines.http://steamcommunity.com/app/286810/discussions/0/540736319869969103/?l=dutch2. modify the main configuration filethis handy little tool allows you to correctly adjust the game resolution for any screen, and can turn off video's that might chrash the game if you have x64.http://www.techpowerup.com/forums/threads/hard-truck-apocalypse-config-editor.201894/3. create a debug profilethere's a chance the ingame menus crash the next time you run HTA and load your last save.Every time HTA starts fresh and before you load a game, start a new game on an empty profile, skip the cutscene andquit to the main menu after the game asks you if you need hints, this appearing of the hints dialog seems to fix this issue until you shut the game down.4. compatibility modeI tend to use the ""vista"" mode, but my experience is that it only somehow helps the first time you need to pass a loading screen,  after that the game seems to work without it until you uninstall it.another thing, SAVE OFTEN and don't be afraid to use console commands when the game breaks you! (example: game physics suddenly decide to hold you hostage on top of a lootcrate just above the ground, bandits keep spawning and eating away your hp, game logic doesn't understand you're stuck; you rage and abandon hours of progress)this game can be very very punishing even with cheats."
