76561198051306254,Recommended,285500,26303634,"Posted: 29 October, 2016",all,Nova773,"DO NOT USE IN-GAME ANISOTROPIC FILTERING, OR U WILL GET UNHANDLED EXCEPTIONS.ONLY USE TRILINEAR FILTERINGForce Anisotropic Filtering in the driver settings of ur graphics card.once you set it up as above, it runs fine.i can play for hours. great physics. great combat. amazing areas to explore. good customizing.i run it on low graphics settings and it still looks great (less glitching when enemies arrive).climbing insane mountains is hours of endless fun, or you can take the roads and go for ""speed"".trucks have a nice heavy feel. hitting the wrong objects at speed can hurt. a poor landing after too much air can hurt. but if you finesse it, and keep your tires hitting the ground instead of your fenders, you can find 6 wheel bliss. the turbo is great for climbing, btw.explosions are very satisfying as well.a steal at 95 cents (once you set up your Anisotropic Filtering as above)."
